description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and dynamic individual to join our fantastic Integrated Discharge Team as a Discharge Coordinator dealing with diverse discharges and working collaboratively with internal and external partners. You will work as a Discharge Coordinator within an established team of Discharge Coordinators responsible for identifying and facilitating discharges on allocated wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discharging our patients to the right destination in a timely manner is key to maintaining flow throughout the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH) and contributes to a positive patient experience. The Discharge Team is part of the Emergency and Urgent Care Group, responsible for maintaining safe patient flow through the NNUH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Discharge Coordinator will work in close conjunction with the multi-disciplinary team and provide support for patients, and their carers to proactively facilitate timely and safe discharges from hospital to home or care settings. The role will include effective communication with Health and Social Care agencies both internally and externally and active involvement in the daily Red to Green Board Rounds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After a period of comprehensive induction you will work on an allocated ward and become an integral part of the ward team with support from Ward Coordinators and supervision of the Specialist Nurses within the Discharge Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a compassionate, motivated individual with excellent communication, interpersonal, organisational and IT skills who is dedicated to working as part of the multidisciplinary team to facilitate safe and timely discharge for our patients, whilst upholding the NNUH PRIDE values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Will include weekend and bank holiday working - 7 day working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 26th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 30th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
